{% extends "base.html" %}

{% block title %}Page Not Found - 404{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<h1>😞 Page Not Found (404)</h1>

<div class="demo-section">
    <h2>🎯 What Happened?</h2>
    <div class="error">
        <p>The URL you requested could not be found. This might happen because:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Invalid path parameter type</strong> - Flask expected a specific type (like integer) but got something else</li>
            <li><strong>Route doesn't exist</strong> - The URL pattern doesn't match any defined routes</li>
            <li><strong>Typo in URL</strong> - Check your URL for spelling mistakes</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="demo-section">
    <h2>🧪 Common URL Parameter Errors</h2>
    
    <h3>Integer Parameter Errors:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><code>/user/alice/posts/abc</code> - Expected integer, got letters</li>
        <li><code>/product/12.5</code> - Expected integer, got decimal</li>
        <li><code>/user/bob/posts/-1</code> - Expected positive integer, got negative</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Missing Parameters:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><code>/user/</code> - Missing username parameter</li>
        <li><code>/product/</code> - Missing product ID parameter</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="demo-section">
    <h2>🔗 Try These Working Examples Instead</h2>
    
    <div class="example-links">
        <a href="/" class="example-link">🏠 Home Page</a>
        <a href="/query-demo?name=Test&age=25" class="example-link">🔍 Query Parameters</a>
        <a href="/user/testuser" class="example-link">👤 User Profile</a>
        <a href="/product/12345" class="example-link">📦 Product Details</a>
        <a href="/search/electronics?q=laptop" class="example-link">🔍 Search Example</a>
        <a href="/request-info" class="example-link">📊 Request Information</a>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="demo-section">
    <h2>💡 URL Parameter Tips</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Check parameter types</strong> - Make sure integers are actually numbers</li>
        <li><strong>Use correct format</strong> - Follow the expected URL pattern</li>
        <li><strong>Test incrementally</strong> - Start with simple URLs and add complexity</li>
        <li><strong>Check documentation</strong> - Review the route definitions for requirements</li>
    </ul>
</div>
{% endblock %}